task.summary: Default task
WIP - writing Auth service

- Change Auth service to use status code to determine whether user was authorised - Remove CORS stuff as it was only being used for dev - Tidy up LoginController & remove Auth specific code
- Change webservice endpoint to remove https
- Added node http-proxy to enable hosting angular resource and webservice under same domain (eliminating need for CORS in dev)
Rename forever script to reflect intended use + remove unsupported String function in proxy script

Added backend for /product and dtos
Hardcoded response for now to aid front end development

Renamed components to fully qualified names using '.', where that is not possible due to angular restrictions I have used the convention '_' as the separator.
Implemented a basic product page using data sourced from a hardcoded ProductController.
Rendered the page using Bootstrap css.
Remove TeamCity reporter from build.

** Product data is now fetched from the database rather than being hardcoded **
Added product and product spec domain objects and database tables.
Update front end product page to include seller (not populated yet) and add to basket button.
Image is broken as I haven't added to backend yet, though front end rendering works when imageUrl is supplied.
Added precursor to "npm run background" so that source is copied to "dist" before running servers (else code can be out of date if npm install not run first).
- Added commons-lang3 to project to support EqualsBuilder and HashCodeBuilder.
Added product end to end test

Added dtos required by product offer front end
Data not yet in database hard been hardcoded in the ProductController
Implemented basic C3.js chart Override JQLite with JQuery to get graph to work - if there's another way to get custom script in an ng-view then we can switch back to JQLite again
Improved grunt watch so it is not watching so many files
fix npm run start-watch (used for CI development)

Added basic 'create order' functionality
Added StubOrderController to enable front end testing of 'create order' functionality
** Switched off CSRF as was blocking postman tests & did not have enough time to resolve - this will need switching back on again asap **
Fix some synchronisation issues when refreshing the page and viewing the login screen.

Merge Scott's bootstrap work into the products page
Added ui bootstrap to project to make bootstrap view tabs work in angular
Fixed C3 dependency error
Implement environment config setup
Fix footer
Fix footer
grunt does not copy all localisation files now to dist, as we only need en-gb - saves about 1000 files !
Fix order placement

Fix order placement
Product price curve chart data is now provided by angular which in turn fetches it from the back end server
move chart code into seperate file
move chart code into seperate file

refactor: move logic out of product controller into service
* New services created Product and Order.
